&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We fuse together exceptional talent who deliver outstanding software solutions. Our approach has helped us grow 60% in 2021, 94% in 2022, while in 2023 we joined forces with Insight, a Fortune 500 company and a leading solutions and systems integrator. With exciting growth plans and cutting-edge projects, there has never been a better time to join our incredible team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Data Engineer to design, build, and maintain the pipelines and data platforms that power company&#39;s next-generation maritime applications. You will work closely with BI Developers, Data Architects, and Product teams to ensure data is collected, transformed, and delivered in a secure, scalable, and efficient manner using Microsoft and Azure technologies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Design, develop, and maintain data pipelines and ETL/ELT processes using Azure Data Factory, Synapse Pipelines, or Databricks.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Build and optimize data lake and data warehouse architectures on the Microsoft Azure platform.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Ensure data quality, reliability, and consistency across all systems through validation, monitoring, and governance practices.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Collaborate with BI Developers and Analysts to deliver high-performance data models for reporting and analytics.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Work with application and integration teams to ingest data from ERP, IoT, APIs, and external sources into the Azure Data Platform.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Implement data security and compliance controls, including identity, access management, and data masking, aligned with maritime regulations.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Optimize pipeline performance and manage cost-efficiency across Azure resources.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Contribute to the automation of deployments using CI/CD, version control, and Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC).&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Stay updated on Microsoft Azure data ecosystem advancements and propose improvements to company&#39;s data architecture.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills and Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, or related field (or equivalent experience).&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• 3–5 years of professional experience as a Data Engineer or in a related role.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Hands-on experience with Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse Analytics, and Azure Data Lake.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Strong proficiency in SQL and experience with Azure SQL Database or SQL Server.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Experience with Databricks (PySpark, SparkSQL) or equivalent data processing frameworks.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Familiarity with data modeling, dimensional design, and data warehouse best practices.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Understanding of Azure DevOps, Git, and CI/CD for data pipeline deployment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Knowledge of Python, T-SQL, or PowerShell for scripting and automation.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ewa-rteLine&quot;&gt;• Familiarity with data governance, lineage, and cataloging tools (e.g., Azure Purview).&lt;/div&gt;
