&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We fuse together exceptional talent who deliver outstanding software solutions. Our approach has helped us grow 60% in 2021, 94% in 2022, while in 2023 we joined forces with Insight, a Fortune 500 company and a leading solutions and systems integrator. With exciting growth plans and cutting-edge projects, there has never been a better time to join our incredible team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data &amp;amp; Information Architect is accountable for defining and embedding a shared Data &amp;amp; Analytics architecture. This role provides practical architectural guardrails, establishes clear ownership and decision rights for data domains, and enables analytics use cases to be delivered through standard, compliant patterns - without ad-hoc data handling or policy exceptions. You will work across product, platform, and domain teams to ensure data is modelled consistently, governed effectively, and usable for operational, analytical, and advanced analytics use cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data &amp;amp; Analytics Architecture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, document, and maintain the target Data &amp;amp; Analytics architecture, covering data domains, ingestion pipelines, analytics layers, and access patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the definition of architectural guardrails that explain what teams must do—not just what they must avoid.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide approved (“golden path”) patterns for data ingestion, analytics, and reporting aligned with security, privacy, and governance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common Domain &amp;amp; Canonical Modelling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and govern the Common Domain Model, establishing shared semantic definitions for core maritime concepts such as vessel, seafarer, voyage, cargo, port call, certificate, and contract.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and evolve a technology-neutral Canonical Data Model (CDM) to standardise data exchange for targeted integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistency between operational data models and analytical representations to support reporting and advanced analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ownership, Governance &amp;amp; Decision-Making&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and document clear ownership and stewardship for data domains, datasets, and analytics platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define decision rights and resolve cross-domain data design conflicts in collaboration with domain and platform leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive metadata management, glossary definitions, and lineage standards to improve discoverability, traceability, and regulatory compliance (e.g. IMO, EU MRV, ESG).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Analytics Enablement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the data architecture enables scalable reporting, self-service analytics, and ML-ready data without ad-hoc handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with analytics and data scientists to align data structures, pipelines, and access patterns with real analytical use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance operational and analytical needs across real-time events, reporting, and historical analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Architecture Practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embed data architecture decisions into Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) and architecture review forums.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a bridge between domain experts, product managers, platform teams, and delivery teams to ensure data architecture is understood, adopted, and applied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the evolution of platform-wide architecture standards and review practices.&lt;/

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We fuse together exceptional talent who deliver outstanding software solutions. Our approach has helped us grow 60% in 2021, 94% in 2022, while in 2023 we joined forces with Insight, a Fortune 500 company and a leading solutions and systems integrator. With exciting growth plans and cutting-edge projects, there has never been a better time to join our incredible team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Role Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A technology company formed by aviation and maritime industry leaders delivers advanced digital maritime applications through a unified platform. The Infrastructure Security Engineer strengthens the security of cloud and on‑premises infrastructure by designing, implementing, and monitoring security controls across Microsoft Azure, networks, and containerized environments. The role ensures resilience against cyber threats and compliance with industry and maritime regulations while collaborating with platform, DevOps, and product teams to embed security into all delivery stages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement security controls across Azure infrastructure, Kubernetes clusters, and networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, detect, and respond to infrastructure security incidents using tools such as Microsoft Defender for Cloud, Sentinel, and Azure Security Center.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct vulnerability assessments, patching, and hardening of servers, containers, and cloud services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and enforce identity and access management (IAM), least‑privilege models, and role‑based access controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support secure design of CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure‑as‑code, and containerized workloads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with architects and engineers to conduct security reviews of new systems and deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve logging, monitoring, and alerting frameworks for proactive threat detection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compliance with regulatory and industry frameworks such as GDPR, ISO 27001, and maritime cybersecurity guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide incident response expertise including forensic investigation and root cause analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote security awareness and training for engineering and operations teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills and Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Cybersecurity, Information Systems, or related field (or equivalent experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in infrastructure or cloud security engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Microsoft Azure security services (Defender, Sentinel, Security Center, Key Vault, Azure Policy).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands‑on experience with firewalls, VPNs, WAFs, and intrusion detection/prevention systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with identity and access management including Azure AD, MFA, Conditional Access, and Privileged Identity Management (PIM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with container and Kubernetes security (image scanning, secrets management, runtime policies).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of infrastructure‑as‑code security (Terraform, Bicep, ARM templates).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with monitoring and logging frameworks (Azure Monitor, Log Analytics, ELK/EFK).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of security frameworks and standards (ISO 27001, NIST CSF, CIS benchmarks).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nice‑to‑have exposure to maritime OT/IT systems, IoT security, or safety‑critical environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, incident response, and problem‑solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration abilities with a proactive security‑first mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;To see more roles, &lt;a href=&q

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We fuse together exceptional talent who deliver outstanding software solutions. Our approach has helped us grow 60% in 2021, 94% in 2022, while in 2023 we joined forces with Insight, a Fortune 500 company and a leading solutions and systems integrator. With exciting growth plans and cutting-edge projects, there has never been a better time to join our incredible team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role: Lead AI Business Consultant&lt;br&gt;Location: Dubai / Abu Dhabi - relocation &amp;amp; VISA support available&lt;br&gt;Salary: DOE&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
